# Nordstjernen local phishing/malware blocklist.
#
# One entry per line: the lowercase SHA-256 hex digest of a hostname,
# optionally followed by whitespace and a comment. A navigation is blocked
# when the digest of its host — or of any of its parent domains — matches an
# entry here, in which case Nordstjernen shows a full-page warning before the
# page is fetched. The check is performed entirely on this device; no part of
# your browsing is ever sent to a remote service.
#
# To add a host, append the digest of its lowercased name, for example:
#   printf '%s' bad.example.com | sha256sum
#
# Replace this file (or ~/.config/nordstjernen/safebrowsing.list, or the file
# named by $NS_SAFEBROWSING_LIST) to keep the list up to date.

ff74d19dbaf39ffe1bcb97536f380d39a979d5057bd4851f08799d83df9bb8ca  # malware.testing.nordstjernen (built-in test entry)
d77d67d13634749b0776161b06f037b8a2bc27c062f0ad212fa3bd3e3f4c52b0  # testsafebrowsing.appspot.com
7e38d942977fdef85525e236c0d2f6a4b1f69c413cb6bb3567487238c3443359  # www.itisatrap.org
be19facbcd16a1e5db0f9ad809727b94c23cad54941b8b6f3b149424f266fc0e  # phishing.example.test
